== Design Notes ==

mymalloc/myfree implementation using a 4096-byte static heap with implicit
free list. Each chunk has an 8-byte header (size_t) where bit 0 encodes
allocation status and the remaining bits encode chunk size (always 8-byte
aligned). Minimum chunk size is 16 bytes (8 header + 8 payload).

Allocation: first-fit scan with block splitting when remainder >= 16 bytes.
All payloads are 8-byte aligned.

Deallocation: validates pointer by walking the chunk list, then marks the
chunk free and coalesces with adjacent free neighbors (both forward and
backward).

Leak detection: registered via atexit() during heap initialization. Walks
the chunk list at exit and reports any still-allocated chunks.

Error detection:
  - free() with non-heap pointer -> exit(2)
  - free() with pointer not at chunk start -> exit(2)
  - double free -> exit(2)
  - malloc() failure -> returns NULL, prints to stderr

== Test Plan ==

correctness.c tests the following requirements:

1. Allocation integrity: allocate 64 objects, fill with distinct byte
   patterns, verify no overlap between allocated objects.
2. Free reuse: fill memory, verify further allocs fail, free one object,
   verify alloc succeeds in the freed space.
3. Forward coalescing: allocate 3 chunks, free all, verify a single large
   allocation succeeds (proving adjacent free chunks were merged).
4. Backward coalescing: free chunks in non-adjacent order (a, b, c with
   gaps), verify full coalescing produces one large free block.
5. Bad pointer detection: free() with a stack pointer exits with status 2.
6. Middle pointer detection: free(p+1) exits with status 2.
7. Double free detection: freeing the same pointer twice exits with status 2.
8. malloc(0) returns NULL.
9. Alignment: all returned pointers are 8-byte aligned.
10. Leak detection: deliberately leaked objects trigger the atexit handler
    (verified via fork + exit status check).

memtest.c (provided): allocates 64 objects filling the heap, writes distinct
patterns, verifies data integrity.

== Test Programs ==

  make              - builds memgrind, memtest, correctness
  ./memgrind        - stress test: 5 workloads x 50 runs, reports avg time
  ./memtest         - basic data integrity test (no arguments)
  ./correctness     - comprehensive correctness test suite (no arguments)

== memgrind Workloads ==

Task 1: malloc() and immediately free() a 1-byte object, 120 times.
Task 2: malloc() 120 1-byte objects into an array, then free() all 120.
Task 3: Randomly interleave malloc/free until 120 allocs done, then free rest.
Task 4: LIFO stack - allocate 120 random-sized (1-16 byte) objects, free in
        reverse order.
Task 5: Linked list simulation - build, traverse, and tear down 12-node lists
        10 times per run.
